Google is said to be in talks with the owner of the Three network to let its users make calls and send texts in any country at no extra cost . 
  Industry sources said the firms are discussing a 'wholesale access agreement' that would help Google create a global network . 
  Customers would be able to use this global network to make calls, send texts and use data as part of their plan . 
  Three already offers a similar scheme called Feel at Home that lets customers use their phones and plans in 18 countries . 
 